                            <comment id="286463" author="eaujames" created="Wed, 2 Dec 2020 09:49:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have the same type of issue for: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/3c2cdeca-b98d-4fc4-9c29-91f28ab07e70&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/3c2cdeca-b98d-4fc4-9c29-91f28ab07e70&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But the test run on x86 architecture.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can it be considered as the same issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="286034" author="simmonsja" created="Wed, 25 Nov 2020 20:03:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Does this mean &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11596&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_42d/test_42e: FAIL: failed: client:143294464 server: 143110144&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11596&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11596&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; now will pass?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="286028" author="adilger" created="Wed, 25 Nov 2020 19:49:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This test has passed 184 times in the past 4 weeks on aarch64, so it must have been fixed by something.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="276437" author="adilger" created="Thu, 30 Jul 2020 21:24:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Grant usage is, by necessity, based on whole PAGE_SIZE usage on the client, since any 1-byte write may cause a &lt;tt&gt;PAGE_SIZE=64KB&lt;/tt&gt; write to the OST.  It &lt;em&gt;should&lt;/em&gt; be accounting for this correctly, but it is entirely possible that there is some assumption on the client or server in the grant usage that needs to be fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
